    dtype=dtype_map,
    blocksize=2**26  # 64 MB blocks for parallel GPU parsing
)
Reason: By sampling just 1 000 rows up front we capture each column’s dtype and pass that explicit dtype map into the full read_csv. This avoids cudf’s full-file type inference cost and yields a single GPU read_csv call. Increasing blocksize to 64 MB reduces the number of parallel parsing tasks and cuts overhead, speeding up the overall CSV load without any CPU fallback.
